sec.p:
We compute CLIPScore [43], [44] to assess image-text alignment. We evaluate $\Delta$-CLIPScore to quantify the improvement in CLIP alignment from caption to explanation. We introduce the delta CLIP score ($\triangle$ CLIP) defined as:
\begin{equation*}
\Delta \text{CLIP}=\operatorname{CLIP}\left(I M G, G_{\text {exp }}\right)-\operatorname{CLIP}\left(I M G, B_{\text {exp }}\right)
\end{equation*}
where $G_{\text {exp }}$ models explanation, and $B_{\text {exp }}$ dataset explanation. Higher $\Delta$ CLIP score indicates stronger improvements in grounding. This follows the general idea of “delta” comparative metrics used in other multimodal contexts [45].
